{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":296979,"duration_api_ms":296614,"num_turns":14,"result":"Written to `/workspace/agent_output/answer.json`. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### Where `flag_value` is processed (`src/click/core.py`, `Option.__init__`)\n\n| Line(s) | What happens |\n|---------|-------------|\n| 2542 | `flag_value` is an **explicit named parameter** (not in `**attrs`) |\n| 2557 | `default_is_missing = \"default\" not in attrs` — captured before `super().__init__()` |\n| 2590–2593 | If `flag_value is not None` → force `is_flag = True` |\n| 2607–2611 | If `is_flag` and `default_is_missing` → auto-set `self.default = False` |\n| 2613–2614 | If `is_flag` and `flag_value is None` → auto-generate `flag_value = not self.default` |\n| 2617–2620 | Type re-inferred from `flag_value` (overwriting type inferred from `default`) |\n| 2749–2758 | **`add_to_parser` ignores `self.flag_value` entirely** for bool flags with secondary opts — hardcodes `const=True`/`const=False` |\n\n### On ordering\n\n**Kwarg ordering does not matter.** `flag_value` is always bound to its explicit parameter; `default` always ends up in `**attrs`; and `\"default\" not in attrs` is an order-independent dict membership check. The ticket's premise is incorrect.\n\n### The real issue\n\nWhen using `--verbose/--no-verbose` (slash notation), `add_to_parser` hardcodes `const=False` for `--no-verbose` regardless of `flag_value`. So `flag_value=True` is **silently ignored** for bool flags with secondary opts — it only matters for single flags (no secondary opts) or the `_flag_needs_value` sentinel path. This creates confusing API surface with no documentation.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"c7a26296-8abe-43d8-ad68-a88b4364e887","total_cost_usd":0.5858574,"usage":{"input_tokens":852,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28363,"cache_read_input_tokens":265569,"output_tokens":15457,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests"